# Terminal Service Configuration
#
# Purpose:
#   This file configures the browser-based setup terminal service, which runs
#   the Stremio Perfect Setup automation in a sandboxed web environment. The service
#   provides Cloudflare Turnstile challenge-based authentication, HMAC-signed
#   session cookies, per-connection isolation via tmpfs workspaces, and automatic
#   session timeouts.
#
# Scope:
#   This configuration file is copied to the VPS and sourced by the Docker
#   Compose setup for the terminal service container. It is populated during
#   the hosting/modules/terminal.sh module hook, which prompts for Turnstile
#   keys and generates secrets if not already present.
#
# Architecture:
#   - server.js (Express gate, Turnstile validation, HMAC cookie signing)
#   - WeTTY subprocess (WebSocket terminal proxy on localhost:3001)
#   - run-session.sh (per-session isolation, sparse clone, main.sh execution)
#
# Cloudflare Turnstile Challenge Configuration
#
# TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY and TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY are required to enable
# challenge-based authentication. Users must pass the Turnstile challenge
# before accessing the terminal interface. This prevents abuse and
# unauthorized access.
#
# To obtain your Turnstile keys:
#   1. Go to https://dash.cloudflare.com/
#   2. In the left sidebar, find "Turnstile" under "AI & ML"
#   3. Click "Create site"
#   4. Enter a name (e.g., "Setup Terminal")
#   5. Choose Challenge Type: "Managed Challenge" (recommended)
#   6. Add Allowed Domains: your domain (e.g., setup.example.com)
#   7. Click Create
#   8. Copy the "Site Key" and paste below as TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY
#   9. Copy the "Secret Key" and paste below as TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY
#
# For testing/development only, you can use Cloudflare's test keys:
#   Site Key:    1x00000000000000000000AA
#   Secret Key:  1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
#   (Note: These keys are for testing and will always pass validation)
#
TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=

# HMAC Cookie Signing Secret
#
# COOKIE_SECRET is auto-generated during installation by hosting/modules/terminal.sh.
# It is used to sign and verify session authentication cookies via HMAC-SHA256.
# This ensures that session tokens cannot be forged or tampered with by clients.
# Do not manually set this value; it is generated securely during setup.
#
COOKIE_SECRET=

# WeTTY Terminal Service Configuration
#
# TERMINAL_MAX_CLIENTS:
#   Maximum number of concurrent terminal sessions allowed. Each active browser
#   connection consumes one client slot. Additional connections will be rejected
#   until a session closes. Default: 5 concurrent sessions.
#
# SESSION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS:
#   Maximum duration (in seconds) a terminal session can remain active. After this
#   time, the session is forcibly terminated and all temporary session data is
#   cleaned up, including the tmpfs workspace and any cloned hosting directory.
#   This is a hard timeout; it triggers even if the terminal is idle.
#   Default: 1800 seconds (30 minutes).
#
TERMINAL_MAX_CLIENTS=5
SESSION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=1800
